{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EWEgcKwCQksGQ18g3eVr12","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bundle kubeconfig points to `http://127.0.0.1:51614` which is the KARMA kubectl proxy. The proxy is a simple HTTP proxy that doesn't support WebSocket upgrades (needed for `exec`, `port-forward`, etc.).\n\nThe oracle script uses `kubectl -n mongodb exec pod -- mongosh ...` which requires WebSocket. Since it goes through the KARMA proxy at port 51614, it fails.\n\nThis is a known issue with the KARMA setup. Looking at CLAUDE.md:\n> \"Direct kubectl invocation is confined to karma/environments/k8s.py and karma/transport/k8s/backend.py.\"\nI need to examine the transport proxy implementation to see whether it can handle exec operations, since it's a TLS-tunneling proxy rather than a simple HTTP proxy.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":747,"cache_read_input_tokens":43110,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":747},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"82f7c5d9-e3c0-48fe-bbb1-a4440e90dd3e","uuid":"8a51e0e0-422d-47ce-a7ac-6a48dc22ba31","request_id":"req_011CbyJqKewMhk49yGp7MMLs"}
